Looking at this problem, I need to prove two parts:
1. For all n ≥ 3, there exists a balanced set of n points
2. The set of n ≥ 3 for which there exists a balanced centre-free set equals the odd numbers ≥ 3

This is a complex combinatorial geometry problem. Let me provide a proof structure:

